# 21. Source framework

This playbook is an original practical synthesis. The following authoritative sources informed its governance, manufacturing, digital-twin, and OT-security posture:

1. [NIST AI Risk Management Framework](https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework) — risk-management foundation for organizations designing, developing, deploying, or using AI.
2. [NIST AI RMF Core and Playbook](https://airc.nist.gov/airmf-resources/airmf/5-sec-core/) — practical framing around Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage.
3. [NIST Generative AI Profile](https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-generative-artificial-intelligence) — GenAI-specific risk considerations.
4. [ISO/IEC 42001:2023](https://www.iso.org/standard/42001) — AI management-system standard.
5. [NIST Smart Manufacturing](https://www.nist.gov/smart-manufacturing) — standards, measurement, and trust considerations for smart manufacturing.
6. [NIST Digital Twins for Advanced Manufacturing](https://www.nist.gov/programs-projects/digital-twins-advanced-manufacturing) — manufacturing digital-twin context and standards direction.
7. [NIST Guide to Operational Technology Security, SP 800-82r3](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/82/r3/final) — OT security considerations addressing reliability, availability, and safety needs.
8. [ISA/IEC 62443 Series of Standards](https://www.isa.org/standards-and-publications/isa-standards/isa-iec-62443-series-of-standards) — industrial automation and control systems cybersecurity practices.
9. [World Economic Forum Global Lighthouse Network](https://initiatives.weforum.org/global-lighthouse-network/home) — examples of manufacturers applying advanced technologies at scale for financial, operational, and sustainability outcomes.
10. [Manufacturing USA: Fundamentals of Smart Manufacturing](https://www.manufacturingusa.com/ewd/fundamentals-smart-manufacturing) — a useful overview of smart manufacturing, IT/OT convergence, digital thread/twin, analytics, AI, and workforce augmentation.

> **Use note:** This playbook does not replace engineering validation, process safety management, quality-system requirements, cybersecurity standards, legal review, export-control assessment, privacy review, or regulatory advice. Apply the organization’s own policies and applicable laws/standards to each use case.
